                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id = "a1">
                        <desc><locus target = "#ir #iv"/> <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አስማት፡</foreign> prayer, insufficiently legible</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a2">
                        <desc><locus target = "#iv"/> <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አስማት፡</foreign> prayer against the devil invoking the Trinity, Christ and the cross. The beginning is not there as the top margin is cut out</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a3">
                        <desc><locus target = "#iv #iir"/> <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አስማት፡</foreign> prayer against the evil eye, <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ሕማመ፡ ዓይን፡</foreign></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a4">
                        <desc><locus target = "#iiv"/> Insufficiently legible <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አስማት፡</foreign> prayer</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a5">
                        <desc><locus target = "#iiir"/> <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አስማት፡</foreign> prayer against stomachache, copied for <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ክፍለ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign> and his wife <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ወለተ፡ ሳሙኤል፡</foreign>,
                        with incipit: <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ቄጼበ፡ ቄፌኑ፡ ብያክ፡ ሞሊ፡ መሞሊ፡...</foreign> </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a6">
                        <desc><locus target = "#iiir"/> What seems a record of transaction of a certain item, insufficiently legible</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a7">
                        <desc><locus target = "#iiiv"/> Prayer to God of David for the protection of several names, in a crude hand</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a8">
                        <desc><locus target = "#2r"/> Note of condolence by <foreign xml:lang = "amh">አባ፡ ዉቤ፡</foreign>Abba Wube</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a9">
                        <desc><locus target = "#163v"/> Prayer for the soul of many people whose names are copied replacing other names</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a10">
                        <desc><locus target = "#183r #183v"/> Psalm 44, obviously a rejected leaf from another Psalter</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a11">
                        <desc><locus target = "#184r #183v"/> Nicene Creed</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a12">
                        <desc><locus target = "#184v"/> <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አስማት፡</foreign> prayer against the evil eye, <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ሕማመ፡ ዓይን፡</foreign>, incomplete at the end</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a13">
                        <desc><locus target = "#185r"/>: Psalm 5:1–5, a rejected leaf from another Psalter</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a14">
                        <desc><locus target = "#71v"/> An erased symbol and an offset line of text mark the midpoint of the Psalter</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a15">
                        <desc>?<locus target = "#161v #162r"/>, etc.: Text is written in the upper margin and a small cross indicates where in the text block it is to be inserted</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a16">
                        <desc type = "OwnershipNote">Note of ownership by <foreign xml:lang = "amh">አዲስ፡ አየነው፡</foreign>, <locus target = "#185r"/></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a17">
                        <desc>
                          Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#41r #49v #132r #132v #139v #149r"/>, etc.);
                          and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#38v #64r #123r #134r #142r"/>, etc.);
                          and in the bottom margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target = "#37r"/>, line 16),
                          and in another case where the symbol (+) is used in the upper margin (<locus target = "#92r"/>, line 3, <locus target = "#157r"/>, line 9,
                          <locus target = "#157v"/>, line 6, <locus target = "#160v"/>, line 4, <locus target = "#161r"/>, line 16, <locus target = "#161v"/>, line 3,
                          <locus target = "#162r"/>, line 5, <locus target = "#163v"/>, line 8)
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a18">
                        <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection
                          of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long,
                          the scribe reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout). This scribe also will
                          complete the line of text above the end of the line (e.g., <locus target = "#7v #18v #21r #22v #39v"/>, etc.)
                        </desc>
                      </item>

                      <item xml:id = "e1">
                        <desc>The general condition of the vellum is dirty and worn</desc>
                      </item>

